title: The Beatles - Public Domain tracks from 1963
description:
Some unreleased recordings by The Beatles weren't published by the EMI before 1 January 2014, and now they fell into the Public Domain in European Union. This is only a portion of them - feel free to redistribute it. You can find complete list of the PD-recordings by The Beatles on various blogs and forums.


01. I Saw Her Standing There - Saturday Club, recorded: 21 May, aired: 25 May 1963,
02. Boys - Saturday Club, recorded: 21 May, aired: 25 May 1963,
03. Long Tall Sally - Saturday Club, recorded: 21 May, aired: 25 May 1963,
04. Do You Want To Know A Secret - Pop Go The Beatles, rec. 24 May, air. 4 June
05. Everybody's Trying To Be My Baby - Pop Go The Beatles, rec. 24 May, air. 4 June
06. From Me To You - Eazy Beat, rec. 19 June, air. 23 June
07. Too Much Monkey Business - Side By Side, rec. 4 April, air. 24 June
08. Twist And Shout - Pop Go The Beatles, r. 17 June, a. 25 June
09. A Shot Of Rhythm And Blues (Eazy Beat, r. 17 July, a. 21 July
10. I'll Get You - Pop Go The Beatles, r. 16 July, a. 13 August
11. She Loves You - Pop Go The Beatles, r. 16 July, a. 13 August
12. You Really Got A Hold On Me - Pop Go The Beatles, r. 16 July, a. 13 August
13. Misery - Pop Go The Beatles, r. 3 September, a. 17 September
14. Christmas Lennon-McCartney Medley - Saturday Club, rec. 17 December, aired 21 December


Sound quality is good for the most of the tracks on this compilation, with the exception for a four rare recordings (04, 05, 09, 14), that are Lo-Fi.
